result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Cases called at 11:21 AM: 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CF603, 22CM376.
Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj in court, in custody with Attorney Robert Allen Thorson.  Attorney Trenton Piltz in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Agreement has been reached. Victim/Witness statute complied with. 
21CM347: Defendant pleads No Contest to an Amended Count 1: Retail Theft-Intentionally Take (<=$500)  (Without Repeater).
21CM371: Defendant pleads No Contest to an Amended Count 1: Retail Theft-Intentionally Take (<=$500)  (Without Repeater) and an Amended Count 2: Misdemeanor Bail Jumping (Without Repeater).
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Defendant is sentenced to Court Costs/surcharges. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
Remaining charges are dismissed and read in.

9:26 AM Cases called: 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CF511, 22CF603 & 22CM376. Prosecuting attorney Loralee Clark in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj in court, in custody.  Attorney Robert Allen Thorson not in court had car trouble. New date set.
Status conference on July 8, 2022 at 11:00 am.

9:37 AM 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CF511, 22CF609 & 22CM376. Prosecuting attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj in court, in custody.  Attorney Robert Allen Thorson in court for Rachel A. Cox-Tuj.
 
22CF511 is an Extradition. Defense has reviewed the fugitive complaint. Defendant would like to waive the Extradition. Defendant signs Waiver. 

Defense requests a quick turn around to possibly resolve other cases before Defendant is transported to Stearns County Minnesota.
Hearing scheduled for July 7, 2022 at 09:30 am.

(9:34 AM cases 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CM376, 22CF511, 22CF603 called.) Prosecuting attorney Afton Brianna Lewis in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj in court, in custody.  Attorney Robert Allen Thorson in court for Rachel A. Cox-Tuj.
Attorney Thorson advises has an offer but isn't inclusive of everything.
Parties address case 22CF511 and Attorney Thorson will reach out to Minnesota.
Court advises will set a new hearing for the extradition paperwork to be signed in court.
Hearing scheduled for July 5, 2022 at 09:30 am.

(9:43 AM cases 21CM347, 21CM371, 22CM376, 22CF511 called.) All parties and court personnel appear via Zoom. 
Prosecuting attorney Trenton Piltz in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Rachel A. Cox-Tuj appeared by phone. Attorney Robert Allen Thorson in court for Rachel A. Cox-Tuj. 
Attorney Thorson advises has offer from the State and needs more time.
Court notes oldest file goes back a year and will not allow any further adjournments after this one.
Parties understand if there is no agreement at the next hearing, cases will need to be scheduled for trial.
Hearing scheduled for June 30, 2022 at 09:30 am.
